  "title": "le, la, l' ou les ?",
  "lesson": "French definite articles agree with the noun: 'le' for masculine, 'la' for feminine, 'les' for plural, and 'l'' before a vowel or silent h (l'ami, l'heure). Unlike English, French keeps the article even when speaking in general (J'aime le café).",
